# Wan Animate Tutorial by HearmemanAI

## Step 1: Load Models
- Download models from Hugging Face  
- **Note:** If using the HearmemanAI RunPod template, models are already pre-loaded  

## Step 2: Setup Your Media
- Load your **reference image** (the person you want to use)  
- Load your **reference video** (the video where you want to replace the person)  
- Set video size (must be divisible by 16)  
  - Recommended: `720x1280` or `480x832`  
- Enter your **text prompt**  

## Step 3: Initial Run
- Run the workflow once  
- The first frame will appear in the **points editor node**  
- Cancel the workflow after this appears  

## Step 4: Mark Areas to Replace
- Place **green points** on areas you want to replace:  
  - Face  
  - Hair  
  - Clothing  
  - Any other parts of the person  

## Step 5: Final Run
- Run the workflow again to generate your **final video**

nodes.title: Positive Prompt
widgets_values: A woman is speaking to the camera
If you're video has audio, connect the node above to audio on the right.

## How to load image 

Run the workflow once, and it will automatically get the first frame of the input video.

## Add new green points

Green points are used to mark the area that you want to detect and replace.
Press the Shift key, then use the left click to add new green points.

## Add new red points

Red points are used to mark the area you want to exclude and preserve in the final video.
Press the Shift key, then use the right click to add new red points.

## Clear all points

Click the **New canvas** to clear all points
